## Why Can't We Just Use Embeddings for Everything?

```
Query: "executeCode"

Embeddings:  text → 384 numbers → search by distance
  "executeCode" → [0.31, 0.72, -0.15, ...]  (384 numbers)
  
  The specific tokens "execute" and "Code" get blended into a 
  384-dimensional average. The exact identity is diluted.

BM25:  text → tokens → exact match
  "executeCode" → ["execute", "code"]
  
  Finds ANY document containing these exact tokens.
  If a function is named executeCode, BM25 will find it 100% of the time.
```

### The Comparison Table

| Query Type | BM25 | Embeddings | Example |
|-----------|------|------------|---------|
| Exact function name | ✅ **Wins** | OK | "validate_input" |
| Exact class name | ✅ **Wins** | OK | "DataProcessor" |
| Meaning/intent | ❌ Loses | ✅ **Wins** | "function that checks if data is valid" |
| Conceptual | ❌ Loses | ✅ **Wins** | "calculate sum of numbers" |
| Mixed | OK | OK | Both contribute |

