## How rank_bm25 Works

```python
from rank_bm25 import BM25Okapi

# Step 1: Build (give it tokenized documents)
corpus = [
    ["validate", "input", "data", "dict"],    # chunk 1's tokens
    ["format", "output", "text", "width"],     # chunk 2's tokens
    ["data", "processor", "class"],            # chunk 3's tokens
]
bm25 = BM25Okapi(corpus)

# Step 2: Search (give it tokenized query)
scores = bm25.get_scores(["validate", "input"])
# → [7.38, 0.0, 1.31]  (chunk 1 scores highest)
```

That's literally the whole library. It handles all the TF/IDF/length math internally.

